IN REPLY REFER TO:
Tribal Operations

Through: Area Director, Anadarko, Oklahoma 73005 July 29, 1969

Mr. Arthur L. Thomas

President, Delaware Executive Committee

Dear Mr. Thomas:

Thank you for sending us copies of Resolution No. 7-68 adopted by 
the General Council of the Delaware Tribe of Indians of Western 
Oklahoma on January 20, 1968.

Resolution No. 7-68 amends the tribe's election procedures by 
changing the date of tribal elections from the first Saturday in 
January to the first Saturday in June, commencing in 1969. The 
resolution also amends the terms of office of the executive committee 
officers. We agree with the Delaware Tribe's decision to stagger 
the terms of officers to provide continuity in the conduct of tribal 
business.

The Delaware Tribe's governing document does not require formal 
approval by this office. However, Resolution No. 7-68, duly 
adopted January 20, 1968, and effective as of that date, by the 
General Council of the Delaware Tribe of Indians of Western 
Oklahoma is hereby given official recognition as Amendment No. I 
to the tribe's governing document. Copies of this letter and of 
Resolution No. 7-68 should be made a permanent part of the tribe's 
organizational document.

Sincerely,

(Sgd.) Charles B. Rovin

Acting Assistant Commissioner
 
 

RESOLUTION

 
 DELAWARE RESOLUTION NO. 7-68

WHEREAS: The Delaware Tribe of Western Oklahoma is organized and has governing rules and 

regulations approved by the Commissioner of Indian Affairs, and

WHEREAS: The Delaware Tribe of Western Oklahoma, after much discussion pertaining to the 
election date of the first Saturday in the month of January of each year as pre
scribed in the original resolution approved August 19, 1958, which is silent on 
amendment provisions, under which the tribe functions, desires to change the dat 
and,

WHEREAS: The Delaware Tribe of Western Oklahoma also desires to change the term of office 

for the election officers so that some will remain in office and there will not 
be a complete change each year for the proper handling of tribal affairs.

NOW BE IT RESOLVED, That the date of next election be the first Saturday in June, 1969, 

with the officers now elected, remaining in office until next election date, 
being the first Saturday in June, 1969,

BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, THAT the election date will be the first Saturday of June of each 

year thereafter,

BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, THAT the terms of the officers will be as follows: President, 

Secretary and One Councilman (to be designated at the June, 1969 election) 
will be elected for a term of two (2) years and the Vice-President, Treasurer 
and One Councilman will be elected for a term of one (1) year. The new terms 
of office will begin with the June, 1969 election date. Thereafter, all terms of 
office shall be for a period of two years or until a successor is duly elected.
 
 

CERTIFICATION

 
 I, Jack McLane, Jr., President of the Delaware Tribe of Indians of Western Oklahoma, cer
tify that the above resolution was passed at a General Council Meeting held in the Anadarko 
Area Office Conference Room, Anadarko, Oklahoma, on the 20th day of January, 1968, at which 
meeting there were 27 voting members present who voted 27 for and 0 against the above said 
resolution amending election rules and regulations.

1-20-68 DATE

Adopted this 20th. day of January, 1968, by the Delaware Tribe of Western 
Oklahoma by a vote of 27 for and 0 against, there being 27 tribal members 
present.
 
  
 

 
AMENDMENT
CONSTITUTION AND BY-LAWS

 
 of the 
 
DELAWARE TRIBE OF WESTERN OKLAHOMA

AMENDMENT I


 
 Article III of the Constitution shall be amended in its entirety which 
shall read as follows: 
 

 ARTICLE III MEMBERSHIP OF TRIBE


Section 1. The membership of the Delaware Tribe of Western Oklahoma shall 
consist of the following persons; provided they have not received land or 
money by virtue of having been enrolled as a member of another Indian 
tribe:

(a)  Those persons who prior to the ratification of this amendment 

qualified for membership under previous membership requirements.

(b)  All persons of Delaware Indian blood who received an allotment 
of land pursuant to the provisions of the Act of March 2, 1895, 
(82 Stat. 876), shall be included as full blood members of the 
tribe.

(c) All living lineal descendants of individuals eligible for 
 membership under the provisions of Section 1 (b) and Section 2 

of the Article, who possess at least one-eighth (1/8) degree 
Delaware Indian blood and one of whose natural parents is a 
member of the Delaware Tribe of Western Oklahoma.

(d)  All persons born on or after the effective date of this Consti

tution and Bylaws, both of whose natural parents are members of 
the Delaware Tribe of Western Oklahoma regardless of degree of 
Delaware Indian blood.

 Section 2. All persons identified in Section 1 (b) of this Article shall 
be considered as possessing 4/4ths degree Delaware Indian blood for the 
purpose of computing eligibility of their descendants for membership under 
Section 1 (c) or 1 (d) of this Article. Brothers and sisters of Delaware 
Indian blood of all persons identified in Section 1 (b) shall likewise 
be considered as possessing 4/4ths degree Delaware Indian blood.

 Section 3. Any person who applies for membership who otherwise qualifies 
for membership but who has been enrolled as a member of another Indian

 tribe may be enrolled as a member of the Delaware Tribe of Western Oklahoma; 
provided he has not shared in land or money as a member of another tribe;
 
 

 
 
 
 and provided further that he relinquishes in writing his membership in 
the other Indian tribe and; provided further, that such applicant is 
admitted to membership by a majority vote of the tribal members in general 
council.

Section 4. The executive committee shall appoint a membership committee 
composed of tribal members who are not members of the executive committee 
which shall have the responsibility of preparing and maintaining the 
current membership roll consistent with the provisions of this Article.

Section 5. The executive committee shall have the power to prescribe 
rules and regulations covering future membership, including adoptions 
and the loss of membership, subject to the approval of the Commissioner 
of Indian Affairs or his authorized representative.
 
 

APPROVAL

 
 I, Charles W. James, Area Director do hereby approve the fore

going Amendment I to the Constitution and By-Laws of the Delaware 

Tribe of Western Oklahoma.

Approval Recommended:

(Sgd) Charles V. Delaney

