AMENDMENT 

CONSTITUTION AND BYLAWS 
 
 Of the  
 
DELAWARE TRIBE OF WESTERN OKLAHOMA

AMENDMENT IX


Sections 1 and 2 of Article VII of the Constitution and Bylaws of 
the Delaware Tribe of Western Oklahoma shall be amended in their 
entirety to read as follows:
 
 

ARTICLE VII - ELECTIONS

 
 Section 1. Bi-annual Elections. Elections shall be held every 
two years with members being selected to fill three positions on 
the executive committee at each election. These bi-annual elections 
shall become effective in 1977. In order to effectively implement 
this procedure, the term of the executive committee member which 
is scheduled to expire in 1978 shall expire in 1977, and the term 
of the Vice President which is scheduled to expire in 1980 shall 
expire in 1979. All other terms of office of members of the execu
tive committee incumbent at the time this amendment becomes effective 
shall remain unchanged.

Section 2. Date of Elections. Regular elections to fill vacancies 
as terms expire on the executive committee shall be held bi-annually, 
in odd-numbered years, at the regular annual meeting of the general 
council on the third Saturday in June. Persons elected to office 
shall serve four (4) years.
 
 

ARTICLE VIII - MEETINGS

 
 Section 1, Article VIII - Meetings, shall be amended to read as 
follows:

Section 1. Annual meetings of the general council shall be held on 
the third Saturday in June for the purpose of receiving reports and 
transacting any other business which may come regularly before the 
council. Bi-annually in odd-numbered years an election to fill 
vacancies on the executive committee shall take piece as part of 
the annual meeting. Should the executive committee determine that 
it is not possible or appropriate to hold such meetings on the specified 
date, it shall then be held within thirty (30) days following, on a 
data to ba determined by the executive committee; provided, that at 
least ten (10) days’ notice shall be given on such meeting.
 
 

