81-37
 
 

DELAWARE TRIBE OF WESTERN OKLAHOMA

RESOLUTION

 
 WHEREAS, the Delaware Tribe of Western Oklahoma operates in accordance 

with the Constitution and By-Laws adopted by the tribe and 
recognized by the Secretary of the Interior, and

WHEREAS, the Constitution empowers the Executive Committee full authority 

to transact all business in behalf of the tribe, and

WHEREAS, tribal members have expressed their desire to Amend the Delaware 
Tribal Constitution and By-Laws, Article III, Section 1 (b) , (c), 
(d), and new Subsection (e), and Article XIV, Section 4, and

WHEREAS, Article III, Section 1 (b) provides that all persons of Delaware 

Indian blood, who received an allotment of land pursuant to the 
provision of the Act of March 2, 1895, (82 Stat.876) shall be 
included as Full Blood Delaware, and

WHEREAS, Article III, Section 1 (c) provides that all living lineal descen
dants of individuals eligible for membership under the provisions 
of Section 1 (b) and Section 2 of the Article, who possess at 
least l/8th degree of Delaware Indian Blood and one of whose 
natural parents is a member of the Delaware Tribe of Western Okla
homa , and

WHEREAS, Article III, Section 1 (d) provides that "All persons born on or 

after the effective date of this Constitution and By-Laws, both 
of whose natural parents are members of the Delaware Tribe of 
Western Oklahoma regardless of degree of Delaware Indian Blood," 
and

WHEREAS, Article XIV, Section 4, provides that the Treasurer shall keep 

all tribal monies entrusted to his care in a Special Bank Account; 
and that the Treasurer shall keep all the accounts, records, and 
books of all tribal monies, and

WHEREAS, the Proposed Amendments to the Constitution and By-Laws are attached 

and provide Article III, Section 1 (b) that all persons of Absentee 
Delaware Blood who received an allotment of lands under the juris
diction of the Anadarko Area Office, shall be Full Blood Members 
of the tribe and Article III, Section 1 (c) eliminates the require
ment of one (1) natural parent as a member of the Delaware Tribe, 
and

WHEREAS, Proposed Amendment, Article III, Section 1 (d) provides that "all 

persons born on or after the effective date of the Constitution 
both of whose natural parents are members of the Delaware Tribe of 
Western Oklahoma", and

WHEREAS, a New Subsection (e), shall be added to Article III which provides 

that the Delaware Indian Blood shall be shown on the membership 
roll as Delaware Tribe of Western Oklahoma blood, and

WHEREAS, Article III, Section 2 of the Constitution and By-Laws shall be 
Amended accordingly, to provide that the words "Delaware Indian 
Blood: shall hereafter be changed to read "Absentee Delaware Indian 
Blood" in order to be consistent with the working in Section 1, 
Article III, and

WHEREAS, Article XIV, as Amended, will allow the Treasurer to keep tribal 

monies in a Special Bank Account or Individual Indian Money Account 
and the books and records of the Treasurer shall be kept in the 
Tribal Office, and

NOW THEREFORE BE IT RESOLVED, that this Resolution replace the Resolution, 
#81-25, adopted by the Delaware Executive Committee on April 18, 
1981, and

BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Proposed Amendments, included in this 

Resolution, be approved by the Bureau of Indian Affairs and 
that the Superintendent of the Anadarko Agency be authorized 
to conduct a referendum election whereby the eligible voters 
may ratify or reject each of the Two Proposed Amendments to 
the Constitution and By-Laws of the Delaware Tribe of Western 
Oklahoma.
 
 

CERTIFICATION

 
 The foregoing Resolution was adopted by the Delaware Executive Committee 
on May 22, 1981, in Anadarko, Oklahoma, by a vote of 4 
for and 0 against, a quorum being present.

ATTEST:

APPROVED:

Dona K. Thompson, Secretary

Lawrence Snake, President

